OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FA man has appeared in court over the
OL,8,Fviolent Belfast knife attack which
OL,9,Fsparked a wave of protests and
OL,10,Fdisorder in Northern Ireland.
OL,12,FHadi Alodid has appeared before the
OL,13,Fcity's magistrates' court on Wednesday
OL,14,Fmorning.
OL,16,FThe 30-year-old, with an address at
OL,17,FDuncairn Avenue in Belfast, is charged
OL,18,Fwith the attempted murder of Stephen
OL,19,FOgilvy, threatening to kill an NHS
OL,20,Fradiographer on the same day and with
OL,21,Fthe possession of a knife.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FHe appeared in court via videolink. He
OL,8,Frefused legal representation and made
OL,9,Fno reply to charges which were put to
OL,10,Fhim through an Arabic interpreter.
OL,12,FAlodid has been refused bail after a
OL,13,Fdetective told Belfast Magistrates'
OL,14,FCourt there was a fear it would lead
OL,15,Fto "significant public disorder" if he
OL,16,Fwas released due to "strong public
OL,17,Ffeeling" about the incident.
OL,26,@wD@DOUwD@`O]xD@UOUyD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FPolice said they "strongly" opposed
OL,8,Fbail on the grounds that Alodid is
OL,9,Fcharged with an "extremely serious
OL,10,Foffence" that has "garnered serious
OL,11,Fmedia attention".
OL,13,FThe detective said if further offences
OL,14,Fwere committed they would be "serious
OL,15,Fand unpredictable in nature", and said
OL,16,Fthe applicant is from Sudan and has
OL,17,Flinks outside of the jurisdiction.
OL,19,FShe also told the court he may fear
OL,20,Ffor his own safety or fear a possible
OL,21,Flong custodial sentence.
OL,26,@oD@ROUoD@[O]qD@QOUrD@HO]rD@SOUsD@PO]vD@
OL,26,A^OUwD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FThe defendant made no reply.
OL,9,FDistrict judge Stephen Keown said the
OL,10,Frisks were "far too great" and would
OL,11,Fbe "unmanageable by any bail
OL,12,Fconditions", and refused bail due to
OL,13,Fthe risk of reoffending, risk of harm
OL,14,Fto the public, risk of public disorder
OL,15,Fand risk of flight.
OL,17,FHe is next due to appear in court in
OL,18,Ffour weeks' time.
OL,26,@rD@LOUrD@ZO]sD@DOUtD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FHe said those members of the public,
OL,8,Fthe police and the emergency services
OL,9,Fshould be commended.
OL,11,FThis follows an attack in the Kinnaird
OL,12,FAvenue area of north Belfast on Monday
OL,13,Fnight.
OL,15,FThe victim of the stabbing remains in
OL,16,Fserious condition and the court has
OL,17,Fheard he lost his left eye and has
OL,18,Fsevere damage to his right eye in the
OL,19,Fattack as well as deep cuts to his
OL,20,Fhead and face, and long lacerations on
OL,21,Fhis back.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FHis family appealed for privacy, but
OL,8,Furged people not to use the attack to
OL,9,F"divide people or fuel hostility".
OL,11,FThe reaction to the incident saw mobs
OL,12,Fset homes, a bus and cars on fire,
OL,13,Fwith people targeted based on their
OL,14,Frace on Tuesday evening.
OL,16,FJudge Stephen Keown warned that anyone
OL,17,Fwho plans to take part in further
OL,18,Fdisorder in Northern Ireland should
OL,19,F"be prepared to go to prison" and said
OL,20,Fthe courts "won't tolerate" any
OL,21,Fattacks on emergency services.
OL,26,@{D@AOU{D@]O]|D@LOU|D@[O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FHe said that the court's thoughts were
OL,8,Fwith the victim, the members of the
OL,9,Fpublic who intervened and the
OL,10,Femergency services who went to the
OL,11,Fvictims' aid.
OL,13,FViolence 'shocking and completely
OL,14,Funacceptable'
OL,16,FThe incident in north Belfast sparked
OL,17,Fa wave of protests and disorder in
OL,18,Fparts of Northern Ireland. There has
OL,19,Fbeen widespread disruption with notice
OL,20,Fof planned protests forcing business
OL,21,Fand schools to close.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
