PN,42209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FThree arrests have been made by midday
OL,8,FWednesday.
OL,10,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer has
OL,11,Fsaid the disorder in Belfast was
OL,12,F"shocking and completely
OL,13,Funacceptable", adding: "It is clear
OL,14,Fthat people were targeted last night
OL,15,Fbecause of their background and I will
OL,16,Fnot tolerate it."
OL,26,@tD@AOUuD@MO]uD@XOUxD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FSpeaking at Prime Minister's
OL,8,FQuestions, he added: "People are
OL,9,Frightly sickened by the horrific
OL,10,Fattack on Monday night in north
OL,11,FBelfast.
OL,13,F"As you have just said, the man
OL,14,Farrested has been in court in Belfast
OL,15,Fthis morning and charged.
OL,17,F"I want to thank the Police Service of
OL,18,FNorthern Ireland and other first
OL,19,Fresponders and members of the public
OL,20,Fwho responded with such bravery, and
OL,21,Four thoughts are with the victim.
OL,26,@pD@VOUuD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,F"But, let me be clear, the acts of
OL,8,Fviolence and arson that followed are
OL,9,Ftotally unjustified.
OL,11,F"This morning I spoke with the First
OL,12,FMinister, the deputy First Minister
OL,13,Fand the Chief Constable, and the
OL,14,FSecretary of State for Northern
OL,15,FIreland is meeting leaders in Belfast
OL,16,Ftoday.
OL,18,F"We are united in calling for calm and
OL,19,Fdetermined to restore order, support
OL,20,Fthe police and all those on the front
OL,21,Fline, and ensure that justice is done."
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOUzD@AOU}D@gO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,423,410,140,120,000,100
PN,42212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1781394469
OL,3,CMan lost eye in Belfast knife attack,
OL,4,Ccourt told as suspect appears before
OL,5,Cjudge
OL,7,FThe PSNI Chief Constable Jon Boutcher
OL,8,Fdescribed the violence as "an act of
OL,9,Fself harm" and an "insult" to the
OL,10,Fbrave actions of those that sought to
OL,11,Fhelp the victim in knife attack.
OL,13,FHe said police would be on the streets
OL,14,Fin greater numbers on Wednesday and
OL,15,Fappealed calm.
OL,17,FSchools in Northern Ireland may have
OL,18,Fto close because of the threat of more
OL,19,Fdisturbances later on Wednesday.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
